com.github.kaktushose.jda.commands.internal

Class YamlLoader

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.github.kaktushose.jda.commands.internal.YamlLoader

  • public final class YamlLoader
extends java.lang.Object
    This class contains methods to create a CommandSettings object from a yaml file.

    To be loaded properly the yaml file must be located in the resources folder and its name must be settings.yaml. If the yaml file deviates from that, this class can be used to load the yaml file manually. Apart from that this class has only an internal purpose and can be ignored.
